Package eu.iv4xr.ux.pxtesting.ltl.offline

Class XState

java.lang.Object
eu.iv4xr.ux.pxtesting.ltl.offline.XState
public class XState extends Object
A generic representation of an agent-state, read from a csv-trace file. A state is assumed to be described a vector of name-value pairs. E.g. a pair (vn,x) represent a variable/property in the state named vn, whose value is x. Only numeric values (float) are supported, with the exception of a property representing time, which is of type long.

Two properties are included as first-class fields: this.pos and this.time to represent the agent's location and the time when the state is sampled. The position is represented as a Vec3 and time is a long. If these information are not available then they will be null.

Other name-value pairs are kept in the field this.values.

An XState can be enriched to contain derived information. See diff and history. The enrichment is done from XStateTrace.enrichTrace(String...).

Author:
Saba, Wish

    • values

      public Map<String,​Float> values
      Key-value pairs representing the value of other variables/properties that make up this state. Only numeric/foat values are supported.

    • diff

      public Map<String,​Float> diff
      For every property name vn, diff.get(vn) is the difference between the value of vn in this state and its value in the "previous" state in the state-trace that contains them. See XStateTrace.enrichTrace(String...).

    • history

      public Map<String,​List<nl.uu.cs.aplib.utils.Pair<eu.iv4xr.framework.spatial.Vec3,​Float>>> history
      We can put here the "history" of a variable/property. Suppose vn is a property whose history we want to track. Then history.get(vn) gives a list of pairs (p,x) of location and the value of vn through out the state-trace that contains this state. See XStateTrace.enrichTrace(String...).
